<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

<title>AI Universe | Generative AI & Agentic AI</title>

<style>
* {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

html {
    scroll-behavior: smooth;
}

body {
    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
    background: #070b18;
    color: white;
    line-height: 1.6;
    overflow-x: hidden;
}

nav {
    position: fixed;
    width: 100%;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 1000;
    background: rgba(7,11,24,.88);
    backdrop-filter: blur(15px);
    padding: 15px 8%;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #28385c;
}

nav h2 {
    background: linear-gradient(90deg,#00e5ff,#9d5cff);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    color: transparent;
}

nav a {
    color: #dce8ff;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-left: 20px;
    transition: .3s;
}

nav a:hover {
    color: #00e5ff;
}

.hero {
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 100px 20px 40px;
    position: relative;
    background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 20% 30%, rgba(0,229,255,.18), transparent 30%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 80% 70%, rgba(157,92,255,.2), transparent 30%);
}

.hero::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    width: 350px;
    height: 350px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0,229,255,.35);
    animation: pulse 4s infinite;
}

.hero-content {
    z-index: 2;
    max-width: 900px;
}

.hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(45px, 8vw, 95px);
    background: linear-gradient(90deg,#00e5ff,#7c5cff,#ff55d7);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    color: transparent;
    animation: float 4s ease-in-out infinite;
}

.hero h3 {
    font-size: 25px;
    margin: 20px 0;
}

.hero p {
    color: #b8c7e8;
    max-width: 750px;
    margin: auto;
}

.button {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 30px;
    padding: 13px 30px;
    border-radius: 30px;
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg,#00a8ff,#8b5cf6);
    transition: .3s;
}

.button:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px) scale(1.05);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 35px rgba(0,229,255,.25);
}

section {
    padding: 90px 8%;
}

.section-title {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 45px;
}

.section-title h2 {
    font-size: 40px;
}

.section-title p {
    color: #94a8cf;
    margin-top: 10px;
}

.grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit,minmax(280px,1fr));
    gap: 25px;
}

.card {
    background: linear-gradient(145deg,#10182d,#0b1122);
    padding: 28px;
    border-radius: 18px;
    border: 1px solid #26385f;
    transition: .35s;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
}

.card::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
    right: -30px;
    top: -30px;
    background: #00e5ff;
    filter: blur(70px);
    opacity: .18;
}

.card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-10px);
    border-color: #00d9ff;
    box-shadow: 0 18px 50px rgba(0,0,0,.35);
}

.card h3 {
    color: #61e8ff;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-size: 23px;
}

.card p {
    color: #b6c4df;
}

.tag {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 15px;
    margin-right: 5px;
    padding: 5px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    background: #182745;
    color: #9feeff;
    font-size: 12px;
}

.compare {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 30px;
}

.compare-box {
    padding: 35px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    background: #10182c;
    border: 1px solid #2c4069;
}

.compare-box h3 {
    color: #00e5ff;
    font-size: 27px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.compare-box ul {
    margin-left: 20px;
    color: #b8c8e5;
}

.flow {
    margin-top: 50px;
    text-align: center;
}

.flow-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 15px;
    margin-top: 30px;
}

.flow-item {
    background: #131f38;
    border: 1px solid #315080;
    padding: 18px 25px;
    border-radius: 15px;
    transition: .3s;
}

.flow-item:hover {
    transform: scale(1.08);
    border-color: #00e5ff;
}

.arrow {
    color: #00e5ff;
    font-size: 25px;
}

.timeline {
    max-width: 850px;
    margin: auto;
}

.timeline-item {
    padding: 25px;
    margin: 20px 0;
    border-left: 3px solid #00e5ff;
    background: #0e172b;
    border-radius: 0 15px 15px 0;
}

.timeline-item h3 {
    color: #61e8ff;
}

footer {
    padding: 35px;
    text-align: center;
    background: #050914;
    color: #7789ac;
    border-top: 1px solid #1c2b49;
}

@keyframes float {
    0%,100% {transform:translateY(0)}
    50% {transform:translateY(-12px)}
}

@keyframes pulse {
    0% {transform:scale(.8);opacity:.2}
    50% {transform:scale(1.2);opacity:.7}
    100% {transform:scale(.8);opacity:.2}
}

@media(max-width:800px) {
    nav .links {
        display:none;
    }

    .compare {
        grid-template-columns:1fr;
    }

    section {
        padding:70px 5%;
    }
}
</style>

</head>

<body>

<nav>
    <h2>AI Universe</h2>

```
<div class="links">
    <a href="#ai">AI</a>
    <a href="#tools">AI Tools</a>
    <a href="#comparison">GenAI vs Agentic AI</a>
    <a href="#architecture">How AI Works</a>
</div>
```

</nav>

<header class="hero">

<div class="hero-content">

<h1>AI UNIVERSE</h1>

<h3>Understanding the Modern Artificial Intelligence Ecosystem</h3>

<p>
Explore Artificial Intelligence, Generative AI, Agentic AI,
ChatGPT, Claude, GitHub Copilot, Codex, BharatGPT and Cursor —
and understand how the AI revolution is changing software,
business and everyday technology.
</p>

<a class="button" href="#ai">Explore AI</a>

</div>
</header>

<section id="ai">

<div class="section-title">
<h2>What is Artificial Intelligence?</h2>

<p>
Artificial Intelligence allows computer systems to perform tasks
that normally require human intelligence.
</p>
</div>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">
<h3>Artificial Intelligence</h3>
<p>
AI is the broad field of creating computer systems capable of
performing intelligent tasks such as understanding language,
recognizing images, making predictions and solving problems.
</p>

<span class="tag">AI</span> <span class="tag">Automation</span>

</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Machine Learning</h3>

<p>
Machine Learning is a branch of AI where systems learn patterns
from data instead of relying entirely on manually programmed rules.
</p>

<span class="tag">ML</span> <span class="tag">Data</span>

</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Deep Learning</h3>

<p>
Deep Learning uses multi-layer neural networks to learn complex
patterns. It powers technologies such as image recognition,
speech recognition and modern large language models.
</p>

<span class="tag">Neural Networks</span>

</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Generative AI</h3>

<p>
Generative AI creates new content such as text, code, images,
audio and video based on patterns learned from large datasets.
</p>

<span class="tag">LLM</span> <span class="tag">Generation</span>

</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Agentic AI</h3>

<p>
Agentic AI goes beyond simply generating an answer.
An AI agent can reason about a goal, plan steps, use available
tools, perform actions and evaluate the results.
</p>

<span class="tag">Agents</span> <span class="tag">Tools</span> <span class="tag">Automation</span>

</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Large Language Models</h3>

<p>
LLMs are AI models trained on very large amounts of text and
other data. They can understand prompts and generate useful
natural-language or code responses.
</p>

<span class="tag">LLM</span> <span class="tag">NLP</span>

</div>

</div>
</section>

<section id="tools">

<div class="section-title">
<h2>Major AI Platforms & Tools</h2>

<p>
Some of the important AI assistants and development tools
used in today's AI ecosystem.
</p>
</div>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">

<h3>ChatGPT</h3>

<p>
ChatGPT is an AI assistant from OpenAI. It can help with
conversation, writing, programming, research, reasoning,
data analysis and many other knowledge tasks.
</p>

<span class="tag">OpenAI</span> <span class="tag">AI Assistant</span>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Claude</h3>

<p>
Claude is an AI assistant developed by Anthropic.
It is designed for tasks such as reasoning, writing,
document analysis, coding and working with large amounts
of information.
</p>

<span class="tag">Anthropic</span> <span class="tag">LLM</span>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>GitHub Copilot</h3>

<p>
GitHub Copilot is an AI coding assistant designed to help
developers write, understand and improve software directly
within development workflows and supported IDEs.
</p>

<span class="tag">Coding</span> <span class="tag">GitHub</span>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>OpenAI Codex</h3>

<p>
Codex is OpenAI's coding-focused AI technology and agent
experience for software development tasks. It can assist with
understanding repositories, generating code, modifying software
and completing development tasks.
</p>

<span class="tag">OpenAI</span> <span class="tag">Coding Agent</span>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>BharatGPT</h3>

<p>
BharatGPT refers to initiatives focused on building AI and
language technologies for India, particularly around Indian
languages and locally relevant AI applications.
</p>

<span class="tag">India</span> <span class="tag">Multilingual AI</span>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Cursor</h3>

<p>
Cursor is an AI-focused code editor that integrates AI assistance
into software development. Developers can use it to understand
codebases, generate code, edit files and work with AI during
development.
</p>

<span class="tag">AI IDE</span> <span class="tag">Developer Tool</span>

</div>

</div>
</section>

<section id="comparison">

<div class="section-title">

<h2>Generative AI vs Agentic AI</h2>

<p>
The difference becomes easier when we look at what happens
after you give the AI a request.
</p>

</div>

<div class="compare">

<div class="compare-box">

<h3>Generative AI</h3>

<ul>
<li>User provides a prompt.</li>
<li>AI understands the request.</li>
<li>AI generates content.</li>
<li>Output may be text, code, images, audio or other content.</li>
<li>The user normally decides what to do with the generated result.</li>
</ul>

<div class="flow-row">

<div class="flow-item">Prompt</div>
<div class="arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-item">AI Model</div>
<div class="arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-item">Generated Output</div>

</div>

</div>

<div class="compare-box">

<h3>Agentic AI</h3>

<ul>
<li>User provides a goal.</li>
<li>AI analyzes the objective.</li>
<li>AI can create a plan.</li>
<li>AI can use available tools.</li>
<li>AI can execute multiple steps.</li>
<li>AI can inspect results and continue toward the goal.</li>
</ul>

<div class="flow-row">

<div class="flow-item">Goal</div>
<div class="arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-item">Plan</div>
<div class="arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-item">Tools</div>
<div class="arrow">→</div>
<div class="flow-item">Action</div>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<div class="flow">

<h2>Simple Example</h2>

<div class="flow-row">

<div class="flow-item">
Generative AI<br>
"Write Python code"
</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="flow-item">
Generates Code
</div>

</div>

<div class="flow-row">

<div class="flow-item">
Agentic AI<br>
"Fix my application"
</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="flow-item">
Inspect Project
</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="flow-item">
Find Problem
</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="flow-item">
Modify Code
</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="flow-item">
Test Result
</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section id="architecture">

<div class="section-title">

<h2>How Modern AI Works</h2>

<p>
A simplified view of the journey from data to an AI-powered application.
</p>

</div>

<div class="flow-row">

<div class="flow-item">Training Data</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="flow-item">Machine Learning</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="flow-item">Neural Networks</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="flow-item">AI Model</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="flow-item">AI Application</div>

</div>

<div class="section-title" style="margin-top:90px">

<h2>Evolution of AI Applications</h2>

</div>

<div class="timeline">

<div class="timeline-item">

<h3>Traditional Software</h3>

<p>
Developers explicitly program rules that determine how
the application behaves.
</p>

</div>

<div class="timeline-item">

<h3>Machine Learning</h3>

<p>
Systems learn patterns from datasets and use those patterns
to make classifications or predictions.
</p>

</div>

<div class="timeline-item">

<h3>Generative AI</h3>

<p>
Models generate new text, software code, images,
audio and other forms of content.
</p>

</div>

<div class="timeline-item">

<h3>Agentic AI</h3>

<p>
AI systems increasingly combine models with tools,
memory, planning and actions to accomplish larger goals.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<footer>

<h3>AI Universe</h3>

<p>
Artificial Intelligence • Generative AI • Agentic AI • AI Development
</p>

<p style="margin-top:10px">
Built using HTML & CSS and ready for cloud deployment.
</p>

</footer>

</body>
</html>
